The paper deals with algorithms for selection queries on arrays, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. This suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the external memory model, which is a common topic in the cs.AL (Algorithms) sub-category. The paper involves analyzing the number of comparisons made by the algorithms, which is a topic in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also discusses the competitive ratio of the algorithms, which is a topic in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing algorithms for efficient search, insertion, and deletion operations, which is a topic in the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category.
